# Project Rules

Before starting any task, read the project rules in this order:

1. `.ai/rules/process.md` - Task management, TDD process
2. `.ai/rules/standards.md` - Coding standards, safety rules, AI behavior
3. `.ai/project.md` - Project overview, tech stack, architecture
4. `.ai/local.md` - Personal/local settings (optional, gitignored)

For detailed commands and folder structure, see `.ai/structure.md`.

## Context Priority

| Priority | Files | When |
|----------|-------|------|
| Always | `rules/process.md`, `rules/standards.md` | Every session |
| For tasks | `project.md`, task file in `.ai/tasks/` | When implementing |
| Reference | `structure.md` | When needing commands/paths |

## Key Rules Summary

### Safety
- Never run destructive commands without permission
- Never start implementation without explicit approval
- Always use test environment for investigation

### Coding
- DRY: Extract code only when used 3+ times
- KISS: Simplest solution that works
- Early returns for edge cases
- No over-engineering

### Process
- Complete question phase before implementation
- Present plan and wait for approval
- TDD: Write failing test first
